[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man in court over £80,000 heroin haul in Aberdeen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man is due to appear in court after £80,000 worth of heroin was recovered in Aberdeen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police made the seizure as part of an intelligence-led operation in the Brucklay Court area of the city on Tuesday.
A mid four-figure sum of cash was also recovered. Police are urging anyone with information to come forward.
A 41-year-old man is expected to appear at Aberdeen Sheriff Court later.
DI Stuart McAdam said: "We rely on support from members of the public to provide us with information and would encourage anyone who has information regarding those dealing drugs to contact Police."
